Causal Policy-Training Schedule Contract V1
Review packet for colleague
Date: 2026-06-04

Context
-------

We found a real future-within-training leakage problem before implementing PPO.

The old policy-training contract was split-aware:

  train_range_digest != validation_range_digest != test_range_digest
  normalization_fit_range_digest == training_range_digest
  replay_buffer_source_range_digest == training_range_digest
  selector_split != test

That was necessary, but not sufficient.

The deeper issue is that full-window upstream training can leak future
information inside the training window itself:

  representation trained on full train window
      -> MDN trained on same train window using representation that saw later
         rows
      -> observer/belief produced from that MDN
      -> policy trained/evaluated on same apparent training window

This means an observation/action at time t may depend on artifacts fitted with
data from times later than t, even though validation/test ranges are disjoint.

The corrected law is:

  For any rollout/training block B_k, every artifact used to produce
  observations, beliefs, actions, rewards, or policy-training trajectories
  inside B_k must have been usable before B_k began.

In contract terms:

  used_artifact.usable_from_key <= block_cursor_begin

and:

  artifacts fitted on B_k must not be used inside B_k.


What We Implemented
-------------------

1. Runtime causal schedule contract
-----------------------------------

New file:

  src/include/kikijyeba/runtime/policy_training_causal_schedule.h

New contract types:

  artifact_fit_ledger_t
  artifact_use_ledger_t
  snapshot_family_t
  causal_training_block_t
  causal_policy_training_schedule_t

Canonical schema:

  kikijyeba.runtime.policy_training_causal_schedule.v1

Supported schedule modes:

  causal_walk_forward_training.v1
      Readiness-grade path.

  offline_full_window_research
      Diagnostic/research only. Cannot satisfy readiness.

  batch_final_refit_candidate
      Final refit candidate. Must declare validation_no_longer_proof and
      sealed_test_required. Cannot itself be the validation proof.

Core validation:

  - missing schedule id/range digests/mode is rejected
  - missing cursor_key_kind is rejected
  - opaque or unsupported cursor key ordering is rejected
  - unsupported mode is rejected
  - same-block snapshot use is rejected
  - future snapshot use is rejected:

      artifact.usable_from_key > block.block_cursor_begin

  - every used snapshot digest must appear in the fit ledger
  - no_future_snapshot_use is derived from artifact fit/use ledgers, not
    trusted as a caller assertion
  - normalization, calibration, covariance/coupler, replay-buffer, and
    reward-baseline future-use are rejected
  - target-label, reward, and trajectory availability cannot be later than
    artifact.usable_from_key
  - causal mode requires at least one training block
  - offline_full_window_research with readiness_eligible=true is rejected
  - batch_final_refit_candidate with readiness_eligible=true is rejected
  - final refit must declare:

      final_refit_uses_validation=true
      validation_no_longer_proof=true
      sealed_test_required=true


