Operative Training Law
----------------------

The readiness-grade schedule is:

  At block B_k start:
      freeze SnapshotFamily_{k-1}

  During B_k:
      observations use prior representation/MDN/observer snapshots
      actions use prior policy snapshot
      Cajtucu executes under the bound paper execution profile
      reward uses the bound reward contract
      trajectory evidence is recorded

  After B_k closes:
      representation, MDN, observer fitted components, normalization, and
      policy may be updated to SnapshotFamily_k

  At B_{k+1}:
      SnapshotFamily_k may become usable

The contract allows block-close joint updates in V1. It does not require strict
staggering across representation -> MDN -> policy generations, as long as the
updated snapshots are not used inside the same block.


What Is Removed From Readiness
------------------------------

The leaky readiness method is no longer accepted:

  full-window representation training
  + full-window MDN training on same range
  + full-window policy training/evaluation on same range
  + calling that readiness evidence

This is now classified as:

  offline_full_window_research

Allowed use:

  diagnostics
  debugging
  ablations
  non-readiness research reports

Forbidden use:

  policy_training_artifact_ready
  policy-training readiness
  rollout readiness
  market readiness
  PPO readiness claims


