Final follow-up implemented:

  We added observed edge-market replay support so new Runtime replay artifacts
  no longer need the synthetic direct-edge fallback for validation rollout.

  Source/runtime propagation added:

    wikimyei.expression.nodelift.srl.node_lifted_batch_t
      carries edge_features and edge_mask from graph anchor source batches

    wikimyei.representation.encoding.vicreg.channel_representation_batch_t
      carries edge_features, edge_mask, and past_keys

    kikijyeba.environment.runtime.replay_source
      persists those tensors into graph_anchor_edge_batch replay artifacts

    kikijyeba.environment.replay.source
      derives a deterministic relative edge market state from observed close
      log-return features in graph-edge order:

        frame 0 edge_mid_price = 1.0
        frame k edge_mid_price = exp(cumulative observed close log return)

      This is explicitly sourced from observed edge features and is different
      from the old synthetic unit-price direct-edge fallback.

  Runtime validation hardening added:

    Runtime report gating now rejects validation_rollout=true if the produced
    replay report has:

      missing report
      completed_count <= 0
      missing execution_profile_digest
      missing policy_set_digest
      cajtucu_synthetic_market_step_count > 0
      cajtucu_invalid_trace_count > 0

    The old attempt_000000 replay remains a useful negative control: it fails
    closed because it produces 1000 synthetic Cajtucu market steps.

  Digest binding fix:

    The replay experiment index writer and Runtime/Lattice inspection path were
    using different digest domains for replay reports.

    Fixed by aligning

      kikijyeba.environment.runtime.experiment_driver::replay_report_digest

    with the Lattice-compatible domain:

      kikijyeba.lattice.exposure.v1
      kikijyeba.environment.replay.report_digest.v1\n<report_text>

    This matters because Lattice readiness already treats report/index digest
    agreement as artifact integrity evidence.

